  "texts": [
    "Nevertheless, our PerceiverMIL achieves a weighted F1 score of 44% on the internal test set (see Figure 4B).",
    "The much larger HistoGPT-1B does not overfit and retains the performance of its vision module.",
    "Surprisingly, the even larger HistoGPT-3B improves the weighted F1 score to 45%.",
    "Compared to the highly specialized models AttentionMIL, TransMIL, and TransfomerMIL, both PerceiverMIL and HistoGPT are slightly better or at least competitive in terms of classification performance.",
    "It is important to note that, unlike MIL approaches, the output of HistoGPT is pure text and not integer class indices, highlighting the flexibility of a vision language model."
